modules.description: Provides gradient-based and derivative-free optimization algorithms for minimizing smooth and non-smooth functions. Works with real-valued vectors and scalar objective functions, supporting bounds and nonlinear constraints. Used to solve parameter estimation problems and numerical optimization tasks in scientific computing.

This module provides optimization algorithms for numerical problems, including global/local search, gradient-based, and derivative-free methods, with specific techniques like MMA, COBYLA, and Nelder-Mead. It operates on float arrays for variables and function values, along with optimization problem instances, enabling constraint handling, bound setting, and parameter tuning. Use cases include solving constrained minimization/maximization problems, configuring algorithm behavior via tolerances and evaluation limits, and monitoring optimization progress through result diagnostics.
